---
import LegalPageLayout from "../layouts/LegalPageLayout.astro";
---

<LegalPageLayout
	title="Privacy"
	description="Privacy policy for Glyph."
	summary="Glyph is built to keep your notes on your device. This page explains what stays local, what may touch third-party services, and how licensing checks work."
>
	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>Short Version</h2>
		<p class="legal-note">Your notes stay on your device. Glyph does not upload, sync, or track your writing by default.</p>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>What Glyph Stores Locally</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Your notes and folders</li>
			<li>Your preferences, settings, and local app data needed to make the app work</li>
			<li>Recent files, appearance choices, and other normal desktop app state</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>What Glyph Does Not Do By Default</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>No cloud sync run by the developer</li>
			<li>No telemetry or analytics run by the developer</li>
			<li>No uploading of your notes to any Glyph server</li>
			<li>No selling of your personal data</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>If you buy Glyph through Gumroad, Gumroad may collect payment and purchase information under its own policies</li>
			<li>If you download Glyph from GitHub, GitHub may log standard site and download information under its own policies</li>
			<li>If you choose to use AI features with your own provider or API key, requests may be sent to that provider under that provider’s terms and privacy policy</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>AI Features</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Glyph may send content you choose to an AI provider only when you use those features</li>
			<li>Those requests go to the provider you choose, not to a hosted Glyph cloud service unless clearly stated otherwise</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>License And Trial Checks</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Official builds may perform limited checks needed to validate trials or licenses</li>
			<li>Those checks are for licensing only and are not used for advertising or behavioral tracking</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>Updates</h2>
		<p>This policy may change over time. When it does, the latest version published on this website will apply.</p>
	</section>

	<section class="legal-section">
		<h2>Contact</h2>
		<p>Privacy questions can be sent to <a href="mailto:karatsidhu@gmail.com">karatsidhu@gmail.com</a>.</p>
	</section>
</LegalPageLayout>
